column4: <content>[recto] P. Breughel II. Hallsborough, Autumn exh. 1966, N° 5 Tower of Babel after PBI, Panel 60 3/4 x 73 1/2 correct 153 cm x 186,7 cm in Minkowski, Text, p. 55, Bild 158 (incomplete); ex. 6 July 1966 Sotheby (127). Correct measurements: to me sent by Mrs. [onleesbaar]: the reproduction in Minkowski and the Hallsborough Catal. incomplete. Town slightly different from Vienna. More at top & sides. The central ""Colosseum"" parts-brick red, the outer shell grey - lash in transition; [verso] Differences when compared with Vienna. The tower moved further back (losing much of its impact). The foreground figures smaller and there is a great deal of space (filled with reduction figures which do not fit the subject) between these foreground group and the tower.</content>
